Class ClassValue.ClassValueMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.WeakHashMap<ClassValue.Identity,ClassValue.Entry<?>>
        • java.lang.ClassValue.ClassValueMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<ClassValue.Identity,ClassValue.Entry<?>>
    Enclosing class:
    ClassValue<T>

    static class ClassValue.ClassValueMap
extends WeakHashMap<ClassValue.Identity,ClassValue.Entry<?>>
    A backing map for all ClassValues, relative a single given type. Gives a fully serialized "true state" for each pair (ClassValue cv, Class type). Also manages an unserialized fast-path cache.

      • INITIAL_ENTRIES

        private static final int INITIAL_ENTRIES
        Number of entries initially allocated to each type when first used with any ClassValue. It would be pointless to make this much smaller than the Class and ClassValueMap objects themselves. Must be a power of 2.

      • findReplacement

        private ClassValue.Entry<?> findReplacement(ClassValue.Entry<?>[] cache,
                                  int home1)
        Clearing a cache slot risks disconnecting following entries from the head of a non-null run, which would allow them to be found via reprobes. Find an entry after cache[begin] to plug into the hole, or return null if none is needed.

      • overwrittenEntry

        private <T> ClassValue.Entry<T> overwrittenEntry(ClassValue.Entry<T> e2)
        Note an entry that is about to be overwritten. If it is not live, quietly replace it by null. If it is an actual null, increment cacheLoad, because the caller is going to store something in its place.
